{{nihongo foot|'''''Miracle Ropitt: 2100-Nen no Daibōken'''''|ミラクルロピット 〜2100年の大冒険〜|lead=yes|group=lower-alpha}}, also called '''''Miracle Ropit's Adventure in 2100''''' on its title screen, is a [[Nintendo Entertainment System|Family Computer]] video game that was released in 1987 exclusively for the [[Japan]]ese market.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://superfamicom.org/famicom/info/miracle-ropits-adventure-in-2100/ | title = English-Japanese title information | publisher = SuperFamicom.org | date = | accessdate = 2011-05-20}}</ref> ''[[The Adventures of Star Saver]]'', also known as ''Rubble Saver'' is a related quasi-sequel for [[Game Boy]].

==Summary==
[[File:MiracleRopitt2100.png|175px|left|thumb|Sample gameplay of ''Miracle Ropitt: 2100-Nen no Daibōken''.]]

The game must be played through twice in order to see the true ending, just like in ''[[Ghosts 'n Goblins]]''.

A [[girl]] in the year 2100 uses a [[robot]] suit. If the player is hit once, then the suit is lost and the player must play as the little girl.<ref name="videogamesmuseum">{{cite web | url = http://www.video-games-museum.com/en/game/Miracle-Ropits-Adventure-in-2100/28/2/5410 | title = Basic overview (in pictures) | publisher = Video Games Museum | date = | accessdate = 2011-05-20}}</ref> One more hit and the player loses a life.<ref name="videogamesmuseum"/> Although the game was only released in Japan, the game's text is in [[English language|English]] and is completely playable by English speakers.

